Shelter Staff made the following comments about this animal:


This is Sasha, a senior labrador retriever mix! According to her foster family, She's GREAT with people of all ages - including rambunctious toddlers! Sasha would make an excellent family dog - she's over the chewing stage, she's housebroken, she knows and listens to commands, she isn't possessive and all she wants out of life is to be loved (and given a tennis ball every once in a while.) She would do better as the only dog in a house, as we're not sure of her history of living with other dogs, and while she's gotten along with the two dogs in her foster home, it took some effort to integrate her. When she's nervous/anxious around other dogs, she becomes a bit of a bully. Cats are out of the picture, unfortunately. What is really great about Sasha is that she's nice and calm in the house, but can work all of her energy out in the yard - she'll even throw a tennis ball to herself to play! She is also a good runner partner/hiker! She needs some leash work, but she's a quick learner, so that should come quickly. This sweet girl deserves an amazing home!

Meet beautiful Heidi! Heidi is a calm, easy, loving, well-behaved girl who likes other dogs. Heidi has been great with the two dogs in her foster home and when meeting new dogs. Heidi is housebroken and well behaved loose in the house when her foster parents go to work, but dances like a happy puppy when they come home. The shelter guesses Heidi is 8 years old. Like many mature GSDs, Heidi has a hitch in her giddy-up. Heidi cannot go for long walks, but she gets around fine at home (up the stairs and through the doggie door, etc.). We have not seen Heidi with cats, but we know she is generally calm, gentle, easy to correct, eager to please and unlikely to catch a cat anyway! I believe Heidi would be fabulous with gentle children, but she may be wary in a bustling, high-noise, high-traffic house. Heidi is looking for a loving home with a soft bed, a human to snuggle with and a doggie friend to nap with.

Shelter Staff made the following comments about this animal:
Miss Lucy Fox is a 3-year-old dog, despite the fact that she looks very much like a little red fox. She's thought to be a pomeranian mix, but may have some schipperke in the family somewhere. Lucy was an owner surrender and came into AAC with a broken leg. Under the care of AAC's wonderful vet staff and her foster family, she is now in wonderful health. She is spayed, vaccinated, and microchipped.

Lucy is very sweet and loves to give kisses. She loves cuddles and likes to be around her people. She has a moderate energy level and likes scamper play. She doesn't seem interested in many toys, but does love to chill out and chew a bone or a Kong. She loves a comfy bed, will crate without issue, and though she's a princess, she likes hikes and doesn't mind getting her feet wet.

She does have a few issues that can be worked on with her new family. When Lucy gets excited or alerted to sound outside, she has a very loud bark. This could be a problem for apartment dwellers, so it is highly recommended that she go to a homeowner. She had little experience with leash walking and is learning quickly, but should be walked on a harness until she gets the hang of things. She is potty trained to a doggy door, but has had 2-3 accidents in the house since she's been with us these past 3 months. Her new family should be patient with her, as sometimes new surroundings and new routines can result in accidents.

Lucy's ideal family would be one who has no small children and has experience with dogs. She is smart and easy to train, but may make mistakes as she gets used to new surroundings. She has a strong prey drive, so a home with cats is probably not recommended, but your yard will be squirrel free with her on patrol. She gets along well with her foster brothers, but has butted heads with our more dominant male dog. She would be a great only dog or with another small, relaxed/submissive dog who enjoys scamper/chase play.

If you are looking for a sweet dog that can work a bow like a supermodel and let down her hair to go hiking along Bull Creek, this is your lady!
